150 Pangani Girls High School alumni gathered for a night of fundraising, networking and dancing at Pride Inn Hotel in Westlands, Nairobi on Friday evening.Present at the dinner was Social Security &amp; Services PS Susan Mochache an alumni who noted, We owe it to the girls to go back and assist where we can, especially through mentorship The event had old girls from as far back as 1975 including Dorothy Nyong o who wore her blazer and was accompanied by her husband Kisumu Senator Anyang Nyong o. Others were A total of Sh200,000 was raised which will go towards the newly set up Pangani Alumni Association Scholarship Fund that assists needy students and provides sanitary towels for girls.